@startuml UseCaseModel
left to right direction
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

actor "Student/Learner\n(Primary)" as Student <<Primary>>
actor "System Admin\n(Secondary)" as Admin <<Secondary>>

rectangle "LearnMesh\nStudy Group Management System" {
  usecase "Register Account" as UC1
  usecase "Login" as UC2
  usecase "Set Learning\nPreferences" as UC3
  usecase "Join Study Group" as UC4
  usecase "Create Study Group" as UC5
  usecase "View Group\nRecommendations" as UC6
  usecase "Match Users\nto Groups" as UC7
  usecase "Manage Users" as UC8
  usecase "Monitor System" as UC9
}

Student --> UC1
Student --> UC2
Student --> UC3
Student --> UC4
Student --> UC5
Student --> UC6

Admin --> UC2
Admin --> UC8
Admin --> UC9

UC6 ..> UC7 : <<include>>
UC4 ..> UC7 : <<include>>
UC3 ..> UC2 : <<extend>>

note right of Student
Primary user who seeks collaborative 
learning through intelligent study groups
end note

note left of Admin
Maintains platform health, manages users,
and monitors system performance
end note

note bottom of UC1
New users create accounts with
username, email, and password
end note

note bottom of UC2
Authenticates users and grants
role-based system access
end note

note top of UC3
Students customize skill level, learning
style, interests, and availability
end note

note top of UC4
Students join groups after compatibility
verification by matching algorithm
end note

note top of UC5
Students create new groups with custom
parameters and become moderators
end note

note top of UC6
AI-driven recommendations based on
student profile and preferences
end note

note right of UC7
Core algorithm matching users to groups
using weighted compatibility factors
end note

note bottom of UC8
Admins can view, edit, suspend, or delete
user accounts and resolve disputes
end note

note bottom of UC9
Admins monitor platform performance, analytics,
and ensure system health and security
end note

@enduml
